Mortgage rates hold steady at record lows — but can you really take advantage of them?
Published: June 27, 2020 at 11:00 a.m. ET
By
Jacob Passy
25
Comments
A cash-out refinance may seem attractive to Americans looking to beef up their financial reserves amid economic turmoil, but there are drawbacks
Low mortgage rates offer the opportunity to build savings through a refinance or save money on a home purchase, but there are risks.
